Why I rejected the live AOR Tokyo Tapes disc (Candidate 1):
- Extended solos and live indulgence conflict with my dislike of sprawling instrumental indulgence. Candidate 1's "extended electric solos" and live AOR format point toward long instrumental passages that bury concise hooks and reduce replayability for my tastes.
- Mid‑forward aggressive guitars and raw front‑of‑mix vocals risk the midrange‑centered intimacy I dislike. While I like punch and preserved dynamics, the emphasis here is on aggressive, mid‑forward guitar tone and raw vocals up front — that tends to pull focus away from tight, groove‑centered mixes and instrumental color (slap echo, upright bass) I prefer.
