- Although Tokyo Tapes does hit some positives (punchy drums, solid low end, preserved dynamics), those attributes are not enough to overcome the mismatch on the decisive points: lack of slap‑back/rockabilly character, extended solos, and live mid‑forward aggression that conflict with my rhythm‑first, hooky, warm‑analog preferences.
Overall, Candidate 2 aligns much more closely with the specific sonic and sequencing characteristics I described — slap‑back echo, upright bass, warm analog sparkle, tightly sequenced radio‑length songs and punchy transient mixes — whereas Candidate 1 skews toward live AOR excesses and midrange aggression that counter my stated dislikes.

